This method ensures attribute safety by first checking if the tag name is recognized in `ATTR_WHITELIST`. If it is, it iterates through all existing attributes to validate and process them against the allowed list.

```python
def parse_attrs(self, tag):
        """
        Reject attributes not defined in ATTR_WHITELIST.
        """
        if tag.name in ATTR_WHITELIST.keys():
            attrs = copy(tag.attrs)
            for attr, value in attrs.items():
                if attr in ATTR_WHITELIST[tag.name]:
                    tag.attrs[attr] = self._parse_attr(tag.name, attr, value)
                else:
                    del tag.attrs[attr]
        else:
            tag.attrs = {}
```

The function maintains a safe state by either modifying the valid attributes via self._parse_attr or completely removing any attribute not listed as permissible.
